$ ----------------------------------------------------------------------
$ Simply-supported square plate under uniform pressure -- SOL 101
$
$ Geometry: 10 in x 10 in plate, t = 0.1 in.
$ Mesh: 5x5 CQUAD4 panel (36 nodes, 25 elements).
$ Material: Al 6061-T6 (E=9.9e6 psi, nu=0.33).
$ Loads: PLOAD2 uniform pressure 1.0 psi pushing in +Z.
$ Constraints: SPC1 123 on all four edges (simply supported -- T1/T2/T3
$              free of rotational restraint).
$
$ Analytical centre deflection (thin plate, Kirchhoff, SS-SS-SS-SS):
$   delta_c = alpha * q * a^4 / D
$   D = E*t^3 / (12*(1-nu^2)) = 9.9e6 * 0.001 / (12*0.8911)
$     = 925.8 lb*in
$   alpha (a/b=1, SS-SS-SS-SS) = 0.00406
$   delta_c = 0.00406 * 1.0 * 10000 / 925.8
$           = 0.0438 in   (centre node 21 T3 should land around this)
$ ----------------------------------------------------------------------
SOL 101
CEND
TITLE = Simply-supported plate - SOL 101 (uniform pressure)
SUBCASE 1
  LOAD = 1
  SPC = 1
  DISPLACEMENT(PRINT,PLOT) = ALL
  STRESS(PRINT,PLOT) = ALL
BEGIN BULK
$
$ -------- Material --------
MAT1           1  9.9+6          .33    .098
$
$ -------- Property (shell, t = 0.1 in) --------
PSHELL         1       1     0.1       1               1
$
